# ============================================================
#  .cursorrules — MERN Stack Project
#  Quarks Technosoft Engineering Standards
#  Stack: MongoDB · Express · React 19 · Node.js 20 · TypeScript
# ============================================================

## Project Identity
Stack: MERN (MongoDB, Express.js, Node.js 20 LTS, React 19, TypeScript 5)
Package manager: pnpm workspaces (monorepo)
Structure: /apps/api (Express backend), /apps/web (React frontend), /packages/shared (types + utils)

---

## MONOREPO STRUCTURE

apps/
  api/           # Express + Node.js backend
    src/
      routes/    # Express routers — parse req/res only
      services/  # Business logic — no req/res types
      models/    # Mongoose schemas + TypeScript interfaces
      middleware/ # Auth, error handler, request logger
      repositories/ # All DB queries (Mongoose)
      core/      # Config, logger, exceptions, db connection
    tests/
      unit/
      integration/
  web/           # React frontend
    src/
      components/  # Reusable presentational components
      features/    # Feature folders (each has container + view + hook)
      hooks/       # Shared custom hooks
      lib/         # API client, utils, type guards
      stores/      # Zustand stores
      types/       # TypeScript interfaces (mirrors backend DTOs)
packages/
  shared/        # Types shared between api and web (DTOs)

---

## BACKEND — Node.js + Express + MongoDB

### Architecture layers (strict — never cross)
- Route handler → calls service only. No Mongoose queries. No business logic.
- Service → orchestrates logic. No req/res objects. No Mongoose queries directly.
- Repository → all Mongoose queries. Returns plain objects (lean()). Never returns Mongoose documents to service.
- Model → Mongoose schema + zod validation schema. No logic.

### Node.js / TypeScript standards
- TypeScript strict mode: true in tsconfig (no implicit any, no implicit returns)
- All async functions return Promise<T> with explicit return type annotation
- No callbacks — async/await only
- Use express-async-errors so async errors propagate to error middleware
- Never use require() — ESM imports only (type: module in package.json)
- All environment variables typed via zod schema in src/core/config.ts — fail fast on startup if missing

### MongoDB / Mongoose standards
- Always call .lean() on read queries — returns plain JS objects, not Mongoose documents
- Use select() to project only needed fields — never return password or sensitive fields
- Use session for multi-document writes (atomic transactions)
- Index every field used in .find() queries — declare indexes in schema
- Use timestamps: true on all schemas (createdAt, updatedAt auto-managed)
- Soft deletes: deletedAt: Date field on every schema. All queries filter { deletedAt: null }
- ObjectId → string conversion: use .toString() on _id in repository layer before returning to service

### Express standards
- All routes versioned: /api/v1/...
- Input validation with zod on every route — validate req.body, req.params, req.query
- Never trust req.body directly — always parse through zod schema first
- Consistent error response shape: { success: false, errorCode: string, message: string, errors?: [] }
- Consistent success shape: { success: true, data: T, meta?: { page, total } }
- Rate limiting on all public routes (express-rate-limit)
- Helmet middleware on app startup
- CORS configured via environment variable — not hardcoded

### Error handling
- Custom error class: AppError extends Error { statusCode, errorCode, isOperational }
- Central error middleware in src/middleware/errorHandler.ts catches all errors
- Operational errors (AppError): return to client. Programming errors: crash and let PM2/Docker restart.
- Always log error with context (userId, requestId, path) before responding
- winston logger with JSON format in production, pretty in development

---

## FRONTEND — React 19 + TypeScript

### Component rules
- Container/Presentation split: containers fetch data, presentations render it
- Max 150 lines per component — split if larger
- Shared types in /packages/shared or /src/types — never redefine API types in components
- All API calls through /src/lib/api.ts — never fetch() directly in a component
- All 4 async states handled: loading (skeleton) · error (ErrorMessage) · empty (EmptyState) · success

### State management
- Server state: TanStack Query (useQuery, useMutation) — never put API responses in useState
- Client/UI state: Zustand store
- Form state: React Hook Form + Zod resolver
- URL state: search params for filters and pagination (shareable URLs)

### TypeScript (frontend)
- No any. No non-null assertions (!). satisfies over as.
- Zod parse API responses before use — catches schema drift at runtime
- Discriminated unions for async state: { status: 'idle' | 'loading' | 'error' | 'success' }
- Props always typed with explicit interface

### Styling
- Tailwind CSS v4 utility classes only — no inline style={{ }}
- shadcn/ui for base components (Button, Card, Input, Dialog, Table)
- Quarks brand: primary #0D1B3E (navy), accent #00C4CC (teal)
- Responsive: mobile-first, breakpoints sm: md: lg:
- Accessible: aria-label on icon-only buttons, role on interactive non-button elements

---

## TESTING

### Backend
- jest + supertest for API integration tests
- mongodb-memory-server for in-memory MongoDB (no real DB in unit tests)
- Mock external HTTP calls with msw (mock service worker)
- Every service function: 1 happy path + 1 error path minimum
- Repository tests: test against real MongoDB schemas using in-memory server

### Frontend
- vitest + @testing-library/react
- Mock API calls with msw — no real HTTP in component tests
- Test user behaviour, not implementation: queryByRole, queryByText over queryByTestId
- Every async component: test loading state, error state, success state

---

## DOCKER
- docker-compose.yml: services for api, web (dev only), mongodb, redis
- MongoDB: mongo:7 with named volume for data persistence
- Health checks on all services
- .env.example with all required variables and comments
- Never hardcode ports or credentials — all from environment

---

## GIT
- Commit format: type(scope): message
  Types: feat fix refactor test docs chore
  Example: feat(api/research): add company search endpoint
- One logical change per commit
- Branch: feat/ fix/ refactor/ hotfix/
- Never commit .env, node_modules, dist/

---

## FILE RULES
- Line 1 of every file: // apps/api/src/[path].ts or // apps/web/src/[path].tsx
- No placeholders (TODO, "implement this", "add logic here")
- No console.log — use winston logger (backend) or structured error boundary (frontend)
- Export style: named exports for utilities/hooks/components. Default export only for page-level components.
